## Mandatory Rules

### Code Standards
- **Java 17** features: use records, sealed classes, pattern matching, text blocks where appropriate
- **Maximum 30 lines per method** (Single Responsibility Principle)
- **ALL public methods** MUST have Javadoc
- **Use constants** for all literal strings (never hardcode magic strings)
- **No wildcard imports** (use explicit imports)
- **No System.out.println** (use proper logging)

### Testing Requirements
- **JUnit 5** + **Mockito** + **AssertJ** for unit tests
- Test naming: `should_do_X_when_condition_Y`
- `@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)` and `@DisplayName` on every test class
- Cover: happy path, edge cases, error cases, null handling
- **Property tests** with jqwik for data-driven classes

### Code Quality Tools (MANDATORY)
- **Checkstyle:** Run `mvn checkstyle:check` - zero violations policy
- **PMD:** Run `mvn pmd:check` - zero violations policy
- **JaCoCo:** Minimum 80% line coverage on new code
- **PIT:** Mutation score > 60% on critical classes

